  "prompt": "What is the process of securing admission at MICA, Ahmedabad?",
  "response": "To secure admission at MICA (Mudra Institute of Communications, Ahmedabad), you need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- Bachelor's degree in any discipline\n- Minimum 50% aggregate marks\n- Valid CAT/XAT/GMAT/GRE score\n\n2. Entrance Exam:\n- MICA requires candidates to take MICAT (MICA Aptitude Test)\n- Tests communication, creativity, and analytical skills\n- Conducted usually in December-January\n\n3. Application Process:\n- Apply online through MICA's official website\n- Fill application form\n- Upload required documents\n- Pay application fee\n- Submit entrance exam scores\n\n4. Selection Stages:\n- MICAT score evaluation\n- Personal Interview (PI)\n- Written Ability Test (WAT)\n- Final merit list preparation\n\n5. Documents Required:\n- Academic mark sheets\n- Entrance exam scorecard\n- Identification proof\n- Passport-sized photographs\n- Work experience certificates (if applicable)\n\n6. Important Dates:\n- Application usually starts in October\n- MICAT conducted in December-January\n- Interview process in February-March\n- Final admission results by March-April\n\nCandidates must prepare thoroughly for MICAT and the interview process to increase their chances of admission.",
